        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between shorthand and longhand border-radius?</button>
            <div class="faq-answer"><p>Shorthand (border-radius: 10px) sets all four corners equally. Longhand properties (border-top-left-radius, border-top-right-radius, etc.) set each corner individually.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What units can I use for border-radius?</button>
            <div class="faq-answer"><p>You can use px (fixed pixels), % (relative to element size), em (relative to font size), or rem (relative to root font size).</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I create pill-shaped buttons with border-radius?</button>
            <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Set border-radius to a large value like 9999px or 50px on a button.</p></div>
